    "body": "To `.to_dlpack()` and `.from_dlpack()` methods in cuDF currently always perform a copy to/from the DLTensor. This is reasonable for DataFrames, as the columns of a dataframe in cuDF are not contiguous in memory, nor are they always of the same data type.\r\n\r\nFor a Series however, I believe we should be able to zero-copy to and from DLPack. That is not the case today:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n>>> import cudf\r\n>>> import cupy as cp\r\n>>> s = cudf.Series([1, 2, 3])\r\n>>> arr = cp.from_dlpack(s.to_dlpack())\r\n>>> s._column.data.ptr\r\n139742968545280\r\n>>> arr.data.ptr\r\n139742968545792\r\n```",
